President Biden spoke at the Wisconsin Black Chamber of Commerce in Milwaukee, highlighting the progress made in supporting Black small businesses. He emphasized the importance of job opportunities for dignity, respect, and the ability to provide for one's family. Biden acknowledged the role of Black small businesses in holding communities together and contributing to the strength of the American economy. He mentioned the record growth in Black business ownership, increased wages, and wealth since the pandemic. The president also discussed his administration's efforts to invest in America, rebuild infrastructure, and create jobs. He highlighted initiatives to address lead exposure, increase federal contract dollars for disadvantaged businesses, and lower prescription drug costs. Biden criticized Republican opposition to these measures and emphasized the need to fight for equal economic opportunity for all Americans. He closed his speech by expressing optimism about America's future and the potential for progress when working together.